Moose::Autobox::Indexed(3) User Contributed Perl Documentation Moose::Autobox::Indexed(3)

NAME

Moose::Autobox::Indexed - the Indexed role

DESCRIPTION

This is a role to describes an collection whose values can be accessed by a key of some kind.

The role is entirely abstract, those which implement it must supply all it's methods. Currently both Moose::Autobox::Array and Moose::Autobox::Hash implement this role.

METHODS

meta

REQUIRED METHODS

at
put
exists
keys
values
kv
slice
each
each_key
each_value

BUGS

All complex software has bugs lurking in it, and this module is no exception. If you find a bug please either email me, or add the bug to cpan-RT.
